		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Dec 19_50</date></p>
			<p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Your esteemed favor of <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> ins. was<lb/> handed to father with my manuscript by <persName>Mr. T. I. Seixas</persName><lb/> and should have had an earlier reply had I not<lb/> been desirous to give you the explanation so asked<add>&#63;</add> for<lb/> from <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> relative to the publication of <persName>Mr. Peynados</persName> letter<lb/> to the Presbyterian Synod&#44; but altho&#39; I am yet unable to furnish<lb/> the explanation you desire&#44; I will no longer delay answering yours<lb/> lest you might attribute my silence to indifference to the<lb/> unmerited outrage inflicted by the Article of the Asmonean.<lb/> I had previously to receipt of your letter seen &#38; read&#44; with<lb/> strong indignation at the foul &#38; scurrilous tone of the writer<lb/> and the petty malignancy of the temper which pervaded it. The<lb/> article signed with the initials of the senior Editor&#44; and tho&#39; I<lb/> felt the strongest desire to step forward in your <sic>defence</sic>&#44;<lb/> I felt that the attack was so personal in its nature that you<lb/> alone&#44; in this case&#44; were the fitter champion of your own reputation.<lb/> I feel however all the delicacy of your position &#38; acknowledge<lb/> that a man whose public life has been passed in active efforts of usefulness<lb/> <del>and</del> to his coreligionists at large&#44; <hi rend="underline">and</hi> the value of whose services<lb/> has been so repeatedly acknowledged on all sides should not want<lb/> friends to step forward to protect him from scurrilous &#38; unmerited<lb/> abuse. <persName>Mr. Schoval</persName> &#38; myself have both been earnestly<lb/> considering the matter and are only at a loss to know thro&#39; what<lb/> channel we might be enabled to present our advocacy to the</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>public eye. The Asmonean will not admit&#44; an antidote to its<lb/> own poison&#44; malignant misconstruction might ascribe any article<lb/> in the Occident to the pen or dictation of its Editor&#44; &#38; thought<lb/> of offering an article to the &#8220;Sunday Times&#8221; the Editor of which<lb/> has always professed the most friendly interest for your<lb/> welfare&#44; &#38; respect for your character&#44; But will he give currency<lb/> to what may tend to the disparagement &#38; infamy of a paper<lb/> of which his Son is associate Editor&#44; but I see no remedy<lb/> but to test him. I shall prepare an article for the Times&#8212;<lb/> and <persName>Mr Schoal</persName> has promised to furnish one for the Occident&#44;<lb/> with regard to <persName>Mr Peynados</persName> letter I called yestermorning at<lb/> the Sanctum of the Asmn. But found only the junior Editor to<lb/> whom in absence of his Senior I showed it&#44; he thought it had been copied<lb/> from the Presbyterian&#44; but on referring to the file found that the Editor<lb/> in a note referred to a private source from which he had derived it.<lb/> I left it with him to be handed <persName>Mr. S.</persName> with a promise that he should<lb/> by letter give the required explanation to <persName>Mr Peynado</persName> &#38; that he would<lb/> likewise furnish me with one&#44; but I am now near the close<lb/> of the second day and have not yet heard from him and think<lb/> it probable that he may feel too indifferent&#44; to give himself the<lb/> trouble.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Isaac&#39;s</persName> apology was sufficiently lame &#38; not at all<lb/> in the <hi rend="underline">terms</hi> in which he expressed himself to me on the subject<lb/> but it was at least an apology&#59; doing you justice if not<lb/> himself</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have nothing of moment to add. All are well<lb/> and desire regards.</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">Yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">E. Block</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
